        // If a[j] > a[i], we found a match. Increment count and advance both pointers.
        // If a[j] <= a[i], a[j] cannot be placed at position i to satisfy the condition.
        // We need a larger element for position i, so we advance j to look for a larger one.
        // We must ensure j is always ahead of or equal to i, and within bounds.
